onnection from i two two to i four two two will not be possible i two two two has been proposed as well several u s highways also pass through the state such as u s route one one us one one us two nine us three one us four three us four five us seven two us seven eight us eight zero us eight two us eight four us nine zero us nine eight us two three one us two seven eight us two eight zero us three three one us four one one and us four three one there are four toll roads in the state montgomery expressway in montgomery tuscaloosa bypass in tuscaloosa emerald mountain expressway in wetumpka and beach express in orange beach ports the port of mobile alabama s only saltwater port is a large seaport on the gulf of mexico with inland waterway access to the midwest by way of the tennessee tombigbee waterway the port of mobile was ranked one two th by tons of traffic in the united states during two zero zero nine the newly expanded container terminal at the port of mobile was ranked as the two five th busiest for container traffic in the nation during two zero one one the state s other ports are on rivers with access to the gulf of mexico water ports of alabama listed from north to south see also outline of alabama organized list of topics about alabama index of alabama related articles lgbt rights in alabama gun rights in alabama right to work law to work in alabama references further reading for a detailed bibliography see the history of alabama atkins leah rawls wayne flynt william warren rogers and david ward alabama the history of a deep south state one nine nine four flynt wayne alabama in the twentieth century two zero zero four owen thomas m history of alabama and dictionary of alabama biography four vols one nine two one jackson harvey h inside alabama a personal history of my state two zero zero four mohl raymond a latinization in the heart of dixie hispanics in late twentieth century alabama alabama review two zero zero two five five four two four three two seven