 applied his work in areas of mathematics and theoretical physics including number theory differential geometry and particle physics awards and honours connes was awarded the fields medal in one nine eight two the crafoord prize in two zero zero one and the gold medal of the cnrs in two zero zero four he was an invited speaker at the icm in one nine seven four at vancouver and in one nine eight six at berkeley and a plenary speaker at the icm in one nine seven eight at helsinki he is a member of the french academy of sciences and several foreign academies and societies including the danish academy of sciences norwegian academy of sciences russian academy of sciences and us national academy of sciences books alain connes and matilde marcolli noncommutative geometry quantum fields and motives colloquium publications american mathematical society two zero zero seven isbn nine seven eight zero eight two one eight four two one zero two alain connes andre lichnerowicz marcel paul schutzenberger jennifer gage translator triangle of thought american mathematical society two zero zero one isbn nine seven eight zero eight two one eight two six one four zero jean pierre changeux alain connes m b debevoise translator conversations on mind matter and mathematics princeton university press one nine nine eight isbn nine seven eight zero six nine one zero zero four zero five one alain connes noncommutative geometry academic press one nine nine four isbn nine seven eight zero one two one eight five eight six zero five see also cyclic homology factor functional analysis higgs boson c algebra m theory groupoid criticism of non standard analysis references external links alain connes official web site containing downloadable papers and his book non commutative geometry isbn zero one two one eight five eight six zero x alain connes standard model an interview with alain connes and a discussion about it one nine four seven births living people two zero th century mathematicians members of the united states national academy of sciences two one st century mathematicians coll ge de france faculty french mathematicians fields medalists mathematical analysts differential geometers cole normale sup rieure alumni vanderbilt university faculty foreign members of the russian academy of sciences members of the french academy of sciences members of the norwegian academy of science and letters members of the royal danish academy of sciences and letters clay research award recipients participants in the les houches physics summer school birth place toronto canada death date death place los angeles united states spouse pauline bush one nine one five one nine one nine marie shelton one nine two seven one nine four nine occupation film directorfilm producerscreenwriter years active one nine one one one nine six one allan dwan three april one eight eight five two eight december one nine eight one was a pioneering canadian born american motion picture director producer and screenwriter early life born joseph aloysius dwan in toronto ontario canada dwan who was the younger son of commercial traveller of woolen clothing joseph michael dwan one eight five seven one nine one seven and his wife mary jane dwan n e hunt moved with his family to the united states when he was seven years old on december four one eight nine two by ferry from windsor to detroit according to his naturalization petition of august one nine three nine his elder brother leo garnet dwan one eight eight three one nine six four became a physician at the university of notre dame allan dwan studied engineering and began working for a lighting company in chicago however he had a strong interest in the fledgling motion picture industry and when essanay studios offered him the opportunity to become a scriptwriter he took the job at that time some of the east coast movie makers began to spend winters in california where the climate allowed them to continue productions requiring warm weather soon a number of movie companies worked there year round and in one nine one one dwan began working part time in hollywood while still in new york in one nine one seven he was the founding president of the east coast chapter of the motion picture directors association career dwan operated flying a studios in la mesa california from august one nine one one to july one nine one two flying a was one of the first motion pictures studios in california history on one two august two zero one one a plaque was unveiled on the wolff building at third avenue and la mesa boulevard commemorating dwan and the flying a studios origins in la mesa california after making a series of westerns and comedies dwan directed fellow canadian american mary pickford in several very successful movies as well as her husband douglas fairbanks notably in the acclaimed one nine two two robin hood dwan directed gloria swanson in eight feature films and one short film made in the short lived sound on film process phonofilm this short also featuring thomas meighan and henri de la falaise was produced as a joke for the two six april one nine two five lambs gambol for the lambs with the film showing swanson crashing the all male club following the introduction of the talkies dwan directed child star shirley temple in heidi one nine three seven and rebecca of sunnybrook farm one nine three eight dwan helped launch the career of two other very successful hollywood directors victor fleming who went on to direct the wizard of oz and gone with the wind and marshall neilan who became an actor director writer and producer over a long career spanning almost five zero years dwan directed one two five motion pictures some of which were highly acclaimed such as the one nine four nine box office hit sands of iwo jima he directed his last movie in one nine six one he died in los angeles at the age of ninety six and is interred in the san fernando mission cemetery mission hills california dwan has a star on the hollywood walk of fame at six two six three hollywood boulevard partial filmography as director the gold lust one nine one one the picket guard one nine one three the restless spirit one nine one three back to life one nine one three bloodhounds of the north one nine one three the lie one nine one four the honor of the mounted one nine one four remember mary magdalen one nine one four discord and harmony one nine one four the embezzler one nine one four the lamb the woman the wolf one nine one four the end of the feud one nine one four the tragedy of whispering creek one nine one four the unlawful trade one nine one four the forbidden room one nine one four the hopes of blind alley one nine one four richelieu one nine one four wildflower one nine one four a small town girl one nine one five david harum one nine one five a girl of yesterday one nine one five the pretty sister of jose one nine one five jordan is a hard road one nine one five betty of graystone one nine one six the habit of happiness one nine one six the good bad man one nine one six an innocent magdalene one nine one six the half breed one nine one six manhattan madness one nine one six accusing evidence one nine one six panthea one nine one seven a modern musketeer one nine one seven headin south one nine one eight mr fix it one nine one eight he comes up smiling one nine one eight getting mary married one nine one nine in the heart of a fool one nine two zero also producer the forbidden thing one nine two zero also producer a splendid hazard one nine two zero robin hood one nine two two zaza one nine two three big brother one nine two three manhandled one nine two four night life of new york one nine two five stage struck one nine two five gloria swanson dialogue one nine two five short film made in phonofilm for the lambs annual gambol held at metropolitan opera house tin gods one nine two six the joy girl one nine two seven east side west side one nine two seven the big noise one nine two eight the iron mask one nine